## Step 5 — Create Ship Unit Item Record

One record per item-pallet assignment. Captures exactly which items (and quantities) went
into each physical Ship Unit.

> **Dependency:** Ship Unit (Step 3) must exist before this record type can reference it.

1. **Customization > Lists, Records & Fields > Record Types > New**
   - Name: `Ship Unit Item`
   - ID: `_lime_ship_unit_item` (NetSuite will prefix with `customrecord`)
   - Allow Inline Editing: Yes
   - Allow Attachments: No
   - Save

2. **Add fields** (on the record type's Fields subtab):

   | Field Label                  | ID (no prefix)           | Type                                         | Required |
   |------------------------------|--------------------------|----------------------------------------------|----------|
   | Ship Unit                    | `_lime_sui_parent`       | List/Record → Ship Unit                      | Yes      |
   | Parent Ship Unit Summary     | `_lime_sui_summary`      | List/Record → Shipment Summary               | No       |
   | Ship Unit Order              | `_lime_sui_order`        | List/Record → Transaction (Transfer Order)   | No       |
   | Item                         | `_lime_sui_item`         | List/Record → Item (all item types, `-10`)   | Yes      |
   | Quantity                     | `_lime_sui_quantity`     | Integer                                      | Yes      |
   | Item Fulfillment             | `_lime_sui_fulfillment`  | List/Record → Transaction (Item Fulfillment) | No       |
   | IF Line #                    | `_lime_sui_line_num`     | Integer                                      | No       |
   | Ship Unit Item Pack Location | `_lime_sui_pack_loc`     | List/Record → Location                       | No       |
   | Ship Unit Item Delivery Location | `_lime_sui_deliv_loc` | List/Record → Location                      | No       |

   > **Parent Ship Unit Summary** links directly to the Shipment Summary for the session — allows searching Ship Unit Items by summary without a sublist join.
   >
   > **Ship Unit Order** links to the Transfer Order the line was drawn from — useful when multiple TOs are packed in a single session.
   >
   > **Item Fulfillment** and **IF Line #** link each packed quantity back to the specific fulfillment line it was pulled from (used for traceability).
   >
   > **Ship Unit Item Pack Location** and **Ship Unit Item Delivery Location** are sourced automatically from the linked Shipment Summary's Location and Delivery Location fields respectively. Configure these as **Source** fields on the record type pointing to the Parent Ship Unit Summary record.

