## Step 8 — Set Custom Record Permissions

Grant **Edit** access on the following custom records to all relevant warehouse roles:

**Applies to:** Ship Unit, Shipment Summary, Ship Unit Item
*(Package Type is read-only for non-admins — do **not** grant Edit on it)*

1. Navigate to **Customization > Lists, Records & Fields > Record Types**
2. Open each of the three record types listed above
3. On the **Access** (or **Permissions**) subtab, add the following roles with **Edit** level:

   | Role                              |
   |-----------------------------------|
   | Lime - WMS Lead                   |
   | Lime - WMS Manager                |
   | Lime - WMS Operator               |
   | Lime - Senior Logistics Analyst   |
   | Lime - Logistics Analyst          |
   | Lime - Logistics Coordinator      |

4. Save each record type.

> Without Edit permission, users in these roles will be unable to create or update
> Ship Unit, Shipment Summary, or Ship Unit Item records during packing/unpacking,
> causing the suitelet to return a permissions error.

