## Step 10 — Testing Checklist

### Pack Orders Flow (Suitelet popup):
- [ ] Open an Item Fulfillment in **Picked** status created from a Transfer Order
- [ ] **"Manage Packing"** button is visible in VIEW mode
- [ ] Clicking the button opens the Pack Orders Suitelet in a popup (1400×800)
- [ ] Screen 1 shows Transfer Orders in Picked status
- [ ] The fulfillment's Transfer Order is pre-selected when opened from the IF record
- [ ] Selecting orders with **different destinations** shows an error and blocks the selection
- [ ] **"Build Pack →"** is disabled until at least one order is selected
- [ ] Selecting an order and clicking "Build Pack →" navigates to the Packing Builder
- [ ] Items panel (left) shows all items from selected fulfillments with quantities
- [ ] Package Type dropdown is populated from `customrecord_lime_package_type` records
- [ ] Weight/Dim Unit dropdowns default per location country (US → LB/IN, non-US → KG/CM)
- [ ] Adding item quantities to a pallet updates the progress bar in real time
- [ ] **"Submit Packing"** remains disabled until all items are assigned 100% across all pallets
- [ ] Over-assigned quantities highlight in red; the item bar turns red
- [ ] Notes textarea accepts text and submits with the payload
- [ ] Submitting creates:
  - [ ] 1 **Shipment Summary** with:
    - [ ] Name set to IF transaction numbers joined by dashes (e.g. `IF-1001-IF-1002`)
    - [ ] Correct pkg count, aggregate weight, packed-by, and summary text
    - [ ] **Location** = Item Fulfillment's "Ship From" location
    - [ ] **Delivery Location** = Transfer Order's "Transfer To" location
    - [ ] **Ship Summary Orders** populated with all selected Transfer Orders
    - [ ] **Ship Summary Fulfillments** populated with all selected Item Fulfillments
    - [ ] **Inventory Status** populated from first inventory-tracked line (blank if no tracked items)
  - [ ] 1 **Ship Unit** per pallet with dimensions, weight, package type, and linked fulfillments
  - [ ] 1 **Ship Unit Item** per item-pallet assignment with quantity, fulfillment line reference, parent summary, and Transfer Order
  - [ ] Note: if the same item is packed from **two different fulfillments** onto the same pallet, **two separate Ship Unit Item records** are created (one per fulfillment line) for full traceability
- [ ] All selected Item Fulfillments updated to **Packed** (`shipstatus = B`)
- [ ] Popup notifies opener; Item Fulfillment page reloads automatically
- [ ] After reload, **"Manage Packing"** button still shows (now opens Unpack flow)

### Unpack Orders Flow (Suitelet popup):
- [ ] Open an Item Fulfillment in **Packed** status
- [ ] **"Manage Packing"** button is visible in VIEW mode (button is hidden on Shipped)
- [ ] Clicking the button opens the Unpack Orders Suitelet in a popup
- [ ] Screen 1 shows Transfer Orders in Packed status; the originating order appears at the top and is pre-ticked
- [ ] Additional orders can be selected or deselected
- [ ] **"Unpack"** button is disabled until at least one order is selected
- [ ] Clicking **"Unpack"** shows a confirmation dialog before proceeding
- [ ] On confirm, all Ship Units linked to the selected TOs are marked Unpacked (no partial selection)
- [ ] All linked Item Fulfillments revert to **Picked** (`shipstatus = A`)
- [ ] Shipment Summary **Unpacked** checkbox set and **Unpacked Date** stamped if all its Ship Units are now unpacked
- [ ] Ship Unit Item records are left intact (not deleted)
- [ ] Success message shows correct package and fulfillment counts
- [ ] Footer shows only a **"Close"** button after successful unpack
- [ ] Popup notifies opener; Item Fulfillment page reloads automatically
- [ ] After reload, **"Manage Packing"** button still shows (now opens Pack flow)

### Navigation Links (Center Category):
- [ ] Transactions tab shows a **Pack Orders** section with "Pack Orders" and "Unpack Orders" links
- [ ] Both links open the respective suitelet directly (no order context required)
- [ ] Opening from navigation (no IF context) shows all eligible orders with none pre-selected

### TMS Saved Search (recommended — create after deployment):
- Navigate to **Reports > Saved Searches > All Saved Searches > New**
- Record Type: **Ship Unit**
- Criteria: `Unpacked` is `false`
- This gives TMS all active (non-reversed) packages for shipment planning.

### OTM Export Saved Search (`customsearch_lime_otm_ship_unit_item_exp`):

This saved search must exist in the target account before OTM integration is active.

| Field        | Value                                              |
|--------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Name         | `***DO NOT MODIFY-OTM SHIPMENT EXPORT`             |
| ID           | `customsearch_lime_otm_ship_unit_item_exp`         |
| Record Type  | **Ship Unit Item**                                 |
| Purpose      | Exports Ship Unit Item data for loading into OTM   |

> **Do not modify this search** — its columns and filters are consumed directly by the OTM integration. Changes to column order, field IDs, or criteria will break the OTM data load.
>
> The search should include at minimum: Ship Unit, Parent Ship Unit Summary, Ship Unit Order, Item, Quantity, Item Fulfillment, IF Line #, Ship Unit Item Pack Location, and Ship Unit Item Delivery Location.

